April, lifting its total investment in the country to $167M. After launching full banking operations on 27 January 2026, the company already reports over 290,000 registered Mexican customers for Q1.\n\nDeposits reached MXN 3,753M (~$200M), driven by competitive interest-bearing accounts. The credit portfolio grew by MXN 44M in low-risk Stage 1 assets, with more than 12,000 active credit card clients.\n\nAsset quality remains pristine: the non-performing loan ratio (IMOR) is just 0.02%, with 99.98% of credit in Stage 1.\n\nLiquidity and capital are equally strong \u2014 Liquidity Coverage Ratio at 1,531% and Capitalisation Index at 141.6%.\n\nAs expected in the heavy investment phase, Revolut Mexico posted a MXN 153M net loss in Q1, fully in line with plan.\n\nCEO Juan Miguel Guerra D\u00e1vila said, \"The response of Mexicans has exceeded our expectations. Clearly, there exists a great appetite for a banking application that offers everything in one place.\"\n\nLooks like Revolut is executing a textbook challenger bank entry in Mexico \u2014 investing capital for growth, maintaining strong capital ratios, and seeing good customer uptake \u2014 despite the expected early losses. But still, it has a huge mountain to climb to become the dominant bank in the country. Let's see if momentul holds.\n\nNubank reported weeks ago that it had reached 15 million customers in Mexico.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 2, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 16, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 1130, "createdAt": "Wed May 06 06:49:48 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 2, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051917329634648231", "displayTextRange": [0, 276], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "maxkarpis", "url": "https://x.com/maxkarpis", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/maxkarpis", "id": "871049780780310528", "name": "Max Karpis", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedTyp